MINIKUBE
(It is a tool used to setup a single node cluster on k8s)

* We need a server with 2 cpus and 4 gb of ram

    1  yum install docker -y && systemctl start docker
        (installing docker is needed)

    (Go to this url to select the installation commandâ€¨https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/?arch=%2Flinux%2Fx86-64%2Fstable%2Fbinary+download)
    (we will get below two commands from this link)
    2  curl -LO https://github.com/kubernetes/minikube/releases/latest/download/minikube-linux-amd64
    3  sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube && rm minikube-linux-amd64

    4  minikube version
    (Check minikube is installed or not)

    5  minikube start --driver=docker --force
    (command to start minikube)

    6  minikube status
    (check the status of minikube)

    7  docker ps
    (we can see a minikube container)
    
    8  curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
    (This is for installing kubectl. Go to below link to copy the command)
    (https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-linux/)

    9 chmod +x kubectl
      (give x permissions to kubectl)
      (we can see this in the above official link)

    10 kubectl version
       (we get "command not found")
    11 mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
       (so we need to move this to its default path)
    12 kubectl version
       (now we can see version)
